blog.name: women-of-sci-fi-and-fantasy
blog.title: Women of Science Fiction & Fantasy
blog.description:
This blog is dedicated to listing the Women of Science Fiction & Fantasy on the Television, the Cinema Screen and in Literature.
I have created this list, as Science Fiction and Fantasy has many fantastic male characters, but the roles that Women play have often seen them in supporting roles or as bit players in a larger story. 
I wanted to recognise all the amazing women who have been a part of the stories, movies and TV programmes that I have enjoyed over the years 
The images in this blog have been chosen to highlight the character, but on occasion, I have had to use photos of the actor.

summary: i didn’t like how arya’s story ended. she basically had 2 antagonists this season: the night king daenerys arya killed the night...
body:
i didn’t like how arya’s story ended. she basically had 2 antagonists this season:

  • the night king
  • daenerys

arya killed the night king after his wights injured but failed to her. daenerys injured arya and, like the night king, she killed people arya was trying to help but arya disappears from the story after reminding jon that daenerys, who just decimated a city, was a really bad person. while i understand why d&d went with jon killing daenerys, the scene we got was very dull and badly written. imagine if arya stepped into the throne room wearing idk a random northerner’s face who came to tell daenerys that he saw an army coming, then he stabs daenerys, removes his face to reveal arya and she takes daenerys’ face because drogon was coming. instead of watching the world’s worst ship for 5 minutes, we could get something spicy
